            documentation if, for example, you decide to run it on your own
            server. This licence doesn't apply to use of the econvenor.org
            service &mdash; that's covered by our <a href='terms'>
            Terms and Conditions</a>.
          p.
            Use of the eConvenor source code and its documentation
            (the "Software") is subject to these conditions:
          p.
            1. The Software must only be used by groups or organisations which
            are not-for-profit, have a progressive focus, are commited to social
            justice and do not aim to spread religion.
          p.
            2. Unions and political parties must pay the eConvenor project an
            annual licence fee to use the Software. Unions and political parties
            must contact the eConvenor project by email and pay the licence fee
